{"word":"H3584 - כָּחַשׁ - kâchash - kaw-khash' - Deceive","slug":"H3584","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּחַשׁ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâchash"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-khash'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Deceive"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D7;&#x05E9;&#x05C1; - ka&#x0302;chash</b> - <i>kaw-khash'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be untrue</i>, in word (to <i>lie</i>, <i>feign</i>, <i>disown</i>) or deed (to <i>disappoint</i>, <i>fail</i>, <i>cringe</i>): - deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-) lie, lying, submit selves."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3585\">H3585</a>, <a href=\"#/H3586\">H3586</a>"}]}